content.description: Crux is right above the small slab finger crack. Can all be dirty during all seasons and cover in stink bugs or lady bugs in the spring.
content.protection: Some small pro at the begining where the finger crack is. Gear runs out in the middle and crux. Then more small pro above the crux and near the top out.
content.location: If your walking away from the Illchester tunnel on the train tracks and look up left you will see the crack. It is possible to hike up to the base. The best way is to set a toperope anchor off the tree and rap down.

content.description: Sunny in the afternoon. Never crowded. Mostly dirty all season and in the spring the upper crack is covered in stink bugs....so watch out!
